{"parentUuid":"471fb029-9dc5-4c84-81d2-904c6bdb1225","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"acae7c0949bec7662","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsKr1cKWjzqu6zpdDxYc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JDHtyDvQJsdSR2jubpkyTw","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\requirements.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":22513,"cache_read_input_tokens":19275,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":22513,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsKqzaZdcjpkLg8AVwaV","attributionAgent":"plan-audit","attributionSkill":"pipeline-orchestration","type":"assistant","uuid":"2cf80cf9-683b-4b61-baab-c0bd8cd6fe43","timestamp":"2026-07-09T23:08:54.404Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"2cf80cf9-683b-4b61-baab-c0bd8cd6fe43","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"895b7771-0494-4fd1-9c42-d5085f2ef142","agentId":"acae7c0949bec7662","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JDHtyDvQJsdSR2jubpkyTw","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Requirements — quota administration (list + delete)\n2\t\n3\t## Resolved\n4\t- How does DELETE /v1/quotas identify the quota? → Query parameters: `DELETE /v1/quotas?customer_id=X&metric=Y`. No request body. The params are validated against the exact same anchored allowlists PUT uses (`CustomerId`, `Metric` in `src/api/schemas/quotas.py`).\n5\t- What does DELETE return when no quota exists for that (customer_id, metric) in the caller's tenant? → 404 with the API's standard error envelope — deletes are explicit, not silently idempotent.\n6\t- What does DELETE return on success? → 204 No Content, no body.\n7\t- Does GET /v1/quotas paginate or filter? → Neither. Full list of the caller's tenant's quotas, deterministically ordered by (customer_id, metric). Per-tenant quota counts are expected to stay small.\n8\t- What does each GET row contain? → Quota definitions only: `{customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}` — the same minimal field set as the existing `QuotaResponse` (no `api_key_id`, no timestamps). Current-window usage stays on the `/v1/usage` endpoints.\n9\t- Who may call GET /v1/quotas? → Admin scope only, same as PUT and DELETE — all of `/v1/quotas` reuses the existing `_require_admin_and_throttled` gate (auth → Tier-2 throttle → admin-scope check).\n10\t- Tenancy → Both endpoints operate strictly within the authenticated principal's own tenant (`api_key_id`), exactly like PUT; no cross-tenant read or delete is possible.\n11\t- DELETE racing an in-flight POST /v1/events → Acceptable. No special synchronization: requests that read the quota before the delete commits may still be rejected against the old cap; enforcement stops for all requests that read after commit. Matches existing PUT-replacement semantics.\n12\t- Non-functional / data / observability defaults confirmed → No new perf budget beyond the API's existing p95 targets; quota rows are non-sensitive operational config (no new data-protection class); deletes are logged through the existing structured-logging conventions.\n13\t\n14\t## Open\n15\t- (none — the operator confirmed the brief is covered; defaults above were accepted explicitly)\n16\t\n17\t## Out of scope\n18\t- Any change to POST /v1/events behavior when no quota exists (the brief pins this: no behavior change).\n19\t- Pagination or filtering on GET /v1/quotas.\n20\t- Including current-window usage/remaining in the quota list.\n21\t- Ingest-scoped read access to quotas (GET is admin-only).\n22\t- Blocking/serializing quota deletion against concurrent ingest enforcement.\n23\t- Resetting or touching recorded usage when a quota is deleted — deletion removes the cap only.\n24\t"}]},"uuid":"3b7c06f6-321d-4fb6-b50e-6000d01c2220","timestamp":"2026-07-09T23:08:54.416Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"2cf80cf9-683b-4b61-baab-c0bd8cd6fe43","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
